org.eclipse.jetty.io

Class SelectorManager.ManagedSelector

  • java.lang.Object
    • org.eclipse.jetty.util.component.AbstractLifeCycle
      • org.eclipse.jetty.io.SelectorManager.ManagedSelector
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    Runnable, Dumpable, LifeCycle
    Enclosing class:
    SelectorManager

    public class SelectorManager.ManagedSelector
extends AbstractLifeCycle
implements Runnable, Dumpable

    SelectorManager.ManagedSelector wraps a Selector simplifying non-blocking operations on channels.

    SelectorManager.ManagedSelector runs the select loop, which waits on Selector.select() until events happen for registered channels. When events happen, it notifies the EndPoint associated with the channel.

        public void submit(Runnable change)

        Submits a change to be executed in the selector thread.

        Changes may be submitted from any thread, and the selector thread woken up (if necessary) to execute the change.

        Parameters:
        change - the change to submit
